# android_architecture.me
# Purpose: Defines the recommended Kotlin/Compose app structure for Book A Dink
#          Android. Specifies layers, module boundaries, state ownership, and
#          backend interaction rules. All rules align strictly with
#          backend_authority.me, data_contracts.me, and client_guardrails.me.
# Scope: Android v1 only

---

## 1. STACK

| Concern | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | Kotlin |
| UI | Jetpack Compose |
| Navigation | Navigation Compose (`androidx.navigation:navigation-compose`) |
| Async | Coroutines + Flow |
| DI | Hilt (`com.google.dagger:hilt-android`) |
| Network | Ktor Client (Kotlin-native) OR Supabase Kotlin SDK (`io.github.jan-tennert.supabase`) |
| Payments | Stripe Android SDK (`com.stripe:stripe-android`) |
| Push | Firebase Cloud Messaging (`com.google.firebase:firebase-messaging`) |
| Image loading | Coil (`io.coil-kt:coil-compose`) |
| In-app browser | Chrome Custom Tabs (`androidx.browser:browser`) |
| Location | FusedLocationProviderClient (Google Play Services) |
| Local storage | DataStore Preferences (`androidx.datastore:datastore-preferences`) |
| Date/time | `java.time` (API 26+; use `desugaring` for API < 26 if targeted) |

---

## 2. LAYER STRUCTURE

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│  UI Layer                           │
│  Composables, Screens, ViewModels   │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Domain Layer                       │
│  Use Cases, State mappers           │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Data Layer                         │
│  Repositories, Data Sources         │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Remote Layer                       │
│  SupabaseService, StripeService,    │
│  FcmService                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Rules:
- UI layer depends on Domain only. Never calls Repository or SupabaseService directly.
- Domain layer depends on Data only. No Compose imports.
- Data layer depends on Remote only. No ViewModel imports.
- Remote layer has zero business logic. Only serialisation, HTTP calls, and error mapping.

