## 9. STATE OWNERSHIP MAP

| State | Owner | Scope |
|---|---|---|
| Auth session | `AppStateHolder` | App-wide |
| Current user profile | `AppStateHolder` | App-wide |
| Credit balances (by club) | `AppStateHolder` | App-wide |
| Clubs list cache | `ClubRepository` | Repository-scoped |
| Games list cache | `GameRepository` | Repository-scoped |
| Bookings cache | `BookingRepository` | Repository-scoped |
| Notifications list | `NotificationRepository` | Repository-scoped |
| Chat posts cache | `ChatRepository` | Repository-scoped |
| Current screen UI state | ViewModel | Screen-scoped |
| Comment draft text | Composable `remember` | Card-scoped (NOT lifted) — see `client_guardrails.me §9` |
| Hold countdown timer | `GameDetailViewModel` | Screen-scoped |
| Stripe PaymentSheet state | `BookingViewModel` | Screen-scoped |

Comment draft MUST be `remember { mutableStateOf("") }` inside the card composable.
Lifting it to the feed ViewModel causes full re-composition of all cards on every keystroke.
This is a known iOS production issue — do not repeat on Android.

---

## 10. ERROR HANDLING STRATEGY

Each layer handles a distinct class of errors:

| Layer | Error Class | Action |
|---|---|---|
| Remote | HTTP errors, network failures | Map to typed `RemoteError` sealed class |
| Repository | `RemoteError` | Map to `DomainError` sealed class; never expose HTTP codes to UI |
| ViewModel | `DomainError` | Map to user-facing string using error catalogue from `ux_parity.me §13` |
| UI | `UiState.Error(message: String)` | Show error banner or retry prompt |

Specific cases:
- HTTP 409 on review insert → `DomainError.ReviewAlreadySubmitted` → "You have already left a review for this session."
- PostgREST 0 rows returned on credit PATCH → `DomainError.InsufficientCredits` → "Insufficient credits. Please try again."
- Stripe `.Failed` → `DomainError.PaymentFailed` → "Payment failed. Please try again."
- HTTP 404 on game fetch → `DomainError.NotFound` → fall back to DB lookup (review flow)

---

## 11. LAYOUT RULES

Android equivalents to iOS layout constraints (see `client_guardrails.me §5`):

- Root screen containers: `Modifier.fillMaxWidth()` on outermost layout composable.
- Every card composable: `Modifier.fillMaxWidth()` before `.background(...)` or `.clip(...)`.
- Avatar preview rows: `LazyRow` with `prefix(N)` equivalent; show `+N` badge for overflow.
  Cap: N satisfying `(N+1) × 44.dp + N × 8.dp ≤ (screenWidth − horizontal padding)`.
- DO NOT use `wrapContentWidth()` on card containers — equivalent to iOS `fixedSize(horizontal: true)`.
- DO NOT set a fixed `width` on a container that holds dynamic text.
- Minimum target width: 360dp (equivalent to iPhone SE 375pt).

