## 12. DEPENDENCY INJECTION SETUP

```
@Module @InstallIn(SingletonComponent::class)
object AppModule {
    @Provides @Singleton fun provideSupabaseClient(): SupabaseClient
    @Provides @Singleton fun provideStripeService(): StripeService
    @Provides @Singleton fun provideAppStateHolder(): AppStateHolder
}

@Module @InstallIn(SingletonComponent::class)
object RepositoryModule {
    @Binds ClubRepository → ClubRepositoryImpl
    @Binds GameRepository → GameRepositoryImpl
    @Binds BookingRepository → BookingRepositoryImpl
    @Binds CreditRepository → CreditRepositoryImpl
    @Binds ProfileRepository → ProfileRepositoryImpl
    @Binds NotificationRepository → NotificationRepositoryImpl
    @Binds ReviewRepository → ReviewRepositoryImpl
    @Binds ChatRepository → ChatRepositoryImpl
}
```

---

## 13. STRIPE ANDROID SETUP

```kotlin
// In Application.onCreate():
PaymentConfiguration.init(context, BuildConfig.STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY)
```

- `STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` comes from `SupabaseConfig` / build config — same value as iOS.
- Google Pay enabled via `GooglePayConfig` with `countryCode = "AU"`, `currencyCode = "aud"`.
- `PaymentSheet.FlowController` used when credits need to be applied before presenting (net price path).
- `PaymentSheet` used for standard full-price booking.
- All PaymentSheet result handling in `BookingViewModel` — no business logic in the Composable.
